parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticky steering issue can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds.

making it difficult to make minor corrections while driving
especially at highway speeds. The steering wheel may stick in a center spot
or may jerk the vehicle around in the lane. Some drivers have reported hearing a pop or creaking sound when the steering wheel is turned.
